http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Kochi/Kerala-High-Court-stays-Lok-Ayukta-order/article14006719.ece

The Kerala High Court on Monday stayed the Lok Ayukta order allowing certain students from Malappuram district to participate in the district school arts festival.The court passed the stay order on a petition filed by the State government against the order of Lok Ayukta setting aside the decision of the Education Department rejecting the appeals against the orders of the district education officials. The Lok Ayukta ordered that the students be allowed to participate in the items. According to the government, the Lok Ayukta had no power to interfere in the conduct of youth festivals.